    • Constructor Detail

      • Vector2D

        public Vector2D(double xSrc,
        double ySrc,
        double theta,
        double speed,
        Entity attachedEntity)
        This constructor is used to generate a vector given a theta value, source position, and speed. This constructor is primarily used for the player ship in which the destination is not known upon creation of the vector.
        Parameters:
        xSrc - The X coordinate of the anchor point.
        ySrc - The Y coordinate of the anchor point.
        theta - The angle away from the x axis in radians
        speed - The magnitude of velocity of this vector.
        attachedEntity - The entity this vector is attached to

      • Vector2D

        public Vector2D(double xOrig,
        double yOrig,
        double xDest,
        double yDest,
        double speed,
        Entity attachedEntity)
        This constructor is used to generate a vector at a given source position, and a given destination position. A theta value is automatically calculated given these data. This constructor is primarily used for vectors which do not change direction over time (ie. projectiles).
        Parameters:
        xOrig - the X origin of this vector
        yOrig - the Y origin of this vector
        xDest - the X destination of this vector
        yDest - the Y destination of this vector
        speed - the magnitude of this vector
        attachedEntity - the entity associated with this vector
